'''Alfredo Zegarra Tejada Florentino''' (born October 16, 1951) is a Peruvian politician and the current mayor of [[Arequipa]]. He has held the post since 2011. From 2003 to 2010, he was mayor of [[José Luis Bustamante District]]. He studied at the [[National University of Saint Augustine]], and is married to Nelly Molina. Before entering politics, he was a [[physician]].<ref>http://peru21.pe/actualidad/arequipa-declaran-reo-contumaz-al-alcalde-alfredo-zegarra-2246884 Peru21</ref>

